<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-3f522b7d0715cd954ba3c87cb7a90fc0bc5512fa">Trolls Glade</h2>
<p>
The Trolls Glade quest entrance appears, only at night, in the forest clearing to the southeast of the main town of Bree. You may need to leave Bree by moving to another map square, or into Overland travel and back, to make the entrance appear. 
</p>
<p>
The quest level itself is quite small: a single room. You enter at the top-left corner. It is mostly forested, though the center is clear and a small path leads out to three corners of the room. The southeast corner of the room has a small open area running northeast to southwest. 
</p>
<p>
Monsters: Forest Trolls, Stone Trolls, Algroths, and the uniques: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Bert the Stone Troll 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Bill the Stone Troll 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Tom the Stone Troll 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
The boys are waiting for you in the southeast part of the room. 
</p>
<p>
Once you kill the first monster, you get a message that you seem to be in the middle of an ambush, and more trolls appear. However, if you have the ability to pass or remove trees, you can pass around the ambush point, and ambush the Trolls yourself! 
</p>
<p>
All you need to do to beat this quest is to kill Tom. He drops good objects. Somewhere on the level, though, is Glamdring, and this is what you need to take back to the Mayor as proof of your success. (Glamdring won't appear until you kill Tom.) 
</p>
<p>
A word to the wise: <em>Be very cautious</em> when turning in Glamdring, if you have a habit of automatically signing up for the next quest when you finish the last one.... 
</p>
